headline: Super Micro Stock Is the Top Performer in the S&P 500 Today. Here’s Why.
summary: Shares of  Super Micro Computer  were rising sharply on Monday, even as the broader market wavered in the wake of uncertainty unleashed by President Donald Trump’s tariffs.  Monday’s gains put Super Micro on pace for its largest same-day percent increase since a 11% jump in March, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  J.P. Morgan noted last week that the company would need to raise its global prices by just 4%, based on the portion of hardware that would be impacted by tariffs.
